The paper deals with coding theory, specifically with complementary information set codes. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the enumeration of quasi-cyclic and quasi-twisted codes, which involves algebraic structures, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions Artin's conjecture, which is related to number theory, making cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the new class of quasi-polycyclic codes, which may fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
